//// **Live IVC golden vectors from the upstream `oaks_txtree`
//// fixture set** — `oaks_txtree_fixtures_v1.tar.gz` delivered
//// 2026-06-26. Source: live Mithril preview aggregator. Each
//// step's Y was generated by appending real preview-network
//// transactions to the previous step's tree, exactly as the
//// production guest will.
////
//// These tests prove our `verify_inclusion` implementation
//// accepts a `tx#0` (first real Mithril tx after the anchor) for
//// each of the 6 steps in the live IVC chain. Each Y is a unique
//// SHA-256 IMT root over real preview-network certified data;
//// each `bound_x` (documented in the section header above each
//// step's constants) is the live Mithril Blake2s tx_merkle_root
//// the validator's UpdateTxtreeTip cross-checks against the
//// system singleton's `current_tip.tx_merkle_root`.
////
//// Coverage: 6 accept tests, one per IVC step. Tampering paths
//// are covered by the existing
//// `tx_inclusion_sha256_vectors.test.ak`; this file is the
//// breadth-coverage companion (proves the verifier works
//// against MULTIPLE Ys, not just one upstream-supplied root).

use aiken/collection/list
use mithril/tx_inclusion_sha256

/// Resolve `zeros[k]` from the module's pinned zero-subtree table.
fn z(k: Int) -> ByteArray {
  expect Some(v) = list.at(tx_inclusion_sha256.zeros, k)
  v
}

// ── live IVC vectors ────────────────────────────────────────────


